ce:section.ce:para:
The detection signal of the probe was taken based on the quenching in the fluorescence profile in the presence of diazinon. In this study, the addition of diazinon into the CDs detection system has caused quenching in the fluorescence intensity with a concentration-dependent manner (Fig. 9
                        ). The limit of detection (LOD) for the proposed detection probe was evaluated to be 0.038 µM. Compared with other sensing platforms for the detection of diazinon in the literature was shown in Table 1
                        . Apparently, the limit of detection obtained in this sensing platform displayed a high sensitivity to diazinon.
